# Schema for the in-cluster rag-agent-api Secret (Article 8).
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#   `kubectl create secret generic rag-agent-secrets --from-env-file=.env.k8s`
#   creates the K8s Secret consumed by `src/ops/deployment/k8s/deployment.yaml`
#   via `envFrom: secretRef: name: rag-agent-secrets`. This .example file
#   documents which keys to put there. The real .env.k8s is gitignored and
#   should never be committed.
#
# WHY ONLY API KEYS HERE (NOT THE FULL .env.local):
#   K8s envFrom precedence: when a key exists in both ConfigMap and Secret,
#   the Secret wins. `.env.local` contains REDIS_URL, CHROMA_URL, POSTGRES_URL
#   pointing at localhost -- if those landed in the Secret they would silently
#   override the in-cluster DNS values from configmap.yaml, and the pods
#   would fail to reach Redis/Chroma. Keep this file's keys disjoint from
#   the configmap's keys (the comments below mark each as such).
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. cp .env.k8s.example .env.k8s
#   2. Fill in each key with your real value
#   3. chmod 600 .env.k8s
#   4. kubectl create secret generic rag-agent-secrets --from-env-file=.env.k8s
#   5. (optional) rm .env.k8s once the Secret is in the cluster
#
# Required (Groq is the default LLM provider per configmap.yaml).
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Optional fallback providers (the LLM client tries them in cost-sorted order
# per src/core/llm_client.py). Leave blank to keep the fallback chain Groq-only.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
COHERE_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
